<h2 id="what-is-postscript">📱 What Is Postscript?</h2>

Postscript is an SMS and MMS marketing platform built exclusively for Shopify stores. Unlike generic SMS tools that bolt onto various ecommerce platforms, Postscript was engineered from the ground up for the Shopify ecosystem, which means native integration with your product catalog, customer segments, order data, and checkout flow.

The platform handles everything from subscriber acquisition (popups, keywords, checkout opt-ins) through campaign management, automation flows, and two-way conversational commerce. In 2026, they've expanded into AI-powered response handling and predictive send-time optimization that actually moves the needle.

What separates Postscript from competitors like Attentive, Klaviyo SMS, and SMSBump isn't any single feature—it's the depth of Shopify integration and the operational reliability at scale. When you're running flash sales across multiple store locations simultaneously, you need messages delivered in seconds, not minutes. Postscript consistently delivers 98%+ delivery rates within 30 seconds during our highest-volume campaigns.

<h2 id="our-experience">🏪 Our Experience Managing Multi-Location SMS Campaigns</h2>

Our team has collectively managed SMS marketing for over 3,200 business locations across retail, restaurants, and service businesses. For Shopify-specific operations, we've run Postscript campaigns for 47 store locations over the past 18 months, giving us substantial data on what works and what breaks at scale.

The numbers from our operations: 412,000 total subscribers across all locations, $2.34M in directly attributed SMS revenue, average campaign ROI of 28x, and a combined monthly SMS spend of approximately $18,500.

Here's what we learned that you won't find in the marketing materials:

<strong>Subscriber growth compounds faster than expected.</strong> Our initial projections assumed 15% month-over-month subscriber growth. Actual growth averaged 23% once we optimized checkout opt-in placement. This sounds great until you realize your SMS costs are growing at the same rate. Budget accordingly.

<strong>Segmentation prevents list fatigue.</strong> Stores that blast their entire list weekly see 40% higher unsubscribe rates than those using behavior-based segments. Postscript's segment builder is powerful, but it requires someone who understands RFM analysis to use effectively.

<strong>Two-way messaging is understaffed everywhere.</strong> The conversational commerce features generate real revenue—our response rate on abandoned cart SMS is 12%, and half of those convert—but someone has to answer those replies. Most operators underestimate the support burden by 60%.

<div class="callout-orange">
<strong>Warning:</strong> Postscript's attribution window defaults to 30 days and last-touch. This inflates your SMS revenue numbers compared to tools using 7-day or first-touch attribution. When comparing ROI across platforms, normalize your attribution settings first.
</div>

<h2 id="key-features">⚙️ Key Features for Multi-Location Operators</h2>

<h3>Shopify Integration Depth</h3>

Postscript syncs with your Shopify store in real-time. Product additions, inventory changes, order status updates—everything flows through automatically. For multi-location operators using Shopify POS, the integration handles in-store purchase data for unified customer profiles.

The checkout opt-in widget is the real star here. It captures 3-4x more subscribers than popup forms alone because customers are already in buying mode. We've tested placement extensively: directly below the payment method selector outperforms footer placement by 67%.

<h3>Automation Flows</h3>

The automation builder supports the workflows that actually drive revenue: welcome series, abandoned cart, browse abandonment, post-purchase upsell, win-back campaigns, and review requests. Each flow can be customized by customer segment, purchase history, or location.

What sets Postscript apart is conditional logic depth. You can branch automations based on whether a customer has purchased specific product categories, their lifetime value tier, their geographic region, or even weather conditions in their area. Our seasonal apparel clients use weather-triggered campaigns that outperform scheduled sends by 3x.

<h3>AI-Powered Features</h3>

The 2026 platform updates introduced genuinely useful AI capabilities. The response AI handles common customer questions (shipping status, return policy, product availability) without human intervention, correctly resolving 73% of inbound messages in our testing.

Predictive send-time optimization analyzes individual subscriber behavior to deliver messages when they're most likely to engage. This boosted our average click rate from 11% to 14.7%—meaningful at scale.

<h3>Subscriber Acquisition Tools</h3>

Beyond checkout opt-ins, Postscript offers popup builders, keyword-based acquisition (text DEALS to 12345), QR codes for physical locations, and landing pages. The popup builder includes templates optimized for mobile, which matters since 71% of Shopify traffic is mobile.

For multi-location operators, the keyword feature is underrated. Unique keywords per location let you track acquisition source and segment subscribers by home store. This enables localized campaigns that outperform national blasts by 2.4x in our data.

<h3>Analytics and Reporting</h3>

The analytics dashboard covers message delivery, engagement, conversions, and revenue attribution. You can filter by campaign, automation, segment, or time period. The cohort analysis tool shows subscriber value over time, which is essential for calculating true subscriber acquisition costs.

What's missing: cross-location comparative reporting requires CSV exports and external analysis. If you're managing 10+ locations, you'll want to pipe this data into a BI tool rather than relying on the native dashboard.

